GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 181
Short Title: Increase Funding for Mobile Crisis Units. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Grafstein (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
February 27, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE FUNDING TO INCREASE THE NUMBER OF MOBILE CRISIS
3 UNITS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
6 Health and Human Services, Division of Mental Health, Developmental Disabilities, and
7 Substance Use Services, the sum of two million dollars ($2,000,000) in recurring funds for each
8 year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium for the purpose of supporting the addition of five new
9 mobile crisis teams with a focus on providing services to the areas of highest need.
10 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
*S181-v-1*

